cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with single image super-resolution using deep convolutional neural networks. The use of deep learning techniques also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves image processing and manipulation, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the proposed two-stage training strategy and loss function optimization suggest that it could also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
